Standard Concurrency Executor Frameworks in java implement -
- FIFO
- Bounded/UnBounded Queue
- Static Priority Queue

But in the situation when the priority of tasks need to be changed dynamically, these frameworks are not suitable.
In such cases, we can implement a custom executor framework that uses a dynamic priority queue.
PriorityBlockingQueue does not automatically re-balance when priority changes,
so we needed a custom dequeue strategy that recalculates effective priority at pick time.